  "debated": [
    {"exercise":"Barbell Deadlift","issue":"Library tags it 'Back', but it is a posterior-chain hip hinge.","decision":"Primary: Glutes, Hamstrings, Lower Back; Secondary: Quads, Traps, Lats, Forearms.","basis":"EMG/coaching consensus: glutes + hamstrings are the prime drivers, erectors mainly resist flexion; quads/traps/lats/forearms assist. Now correctly contributes to BOTH Legs and Back display groups."},
    {"exercise":"Romanian Deadlift / RDL variants","issue":"Library tags 'Back'.","decision":"Primary Hamstrings, Glutes (rolls to Legs); Lower Back secondary (rolls to Back).","basis":"RDL is a hamstring/glute hinge; deliberate accuracy correction vs the single 'Back' tag."},
    {"exercise":"Dumbbell Pullover / Cable Pullover","issue":"Lats-vs-chest debate.","decision":"Primary Lats; Secondary Chest.","basis":"EMG is mixed; classified per the library's 'Back' intent and shoulder-extension mechanics. Could be flipped to Chest-primary if you prefer."},
    {"exercise":"Diamond Push-Up","issue":"Listed TWICE in the library (Chest section and Triceps section), same name.","decision":"One canonical entry: Triceps primary, Chest + Front Delts secondary.","basis":"It's the classic triceps push-up. RECOMMEND removing the duplicate Chest-section library row to avoid a name collision."},
    {"exercise":"Leg Press","issue":"Hamstring credit.","decision":"Primary Quads; Secondary Glutes; hamstrings NOT credited.","basis":"Hamstring involvement is minimal in leg press; foot placement shifts quad/glute emphasis."},
    {"exercise":"Hip Adductor Machine / adductors","issue":"Adductors were not in the original taxonomy.","decision":"RESOLVED — 'Adductors' added as the 17th fine muscle (rolls up to Legs). Hip Adductor Machine maps to Adductors; Sumo Goblet Squat, Side Lunge, and Cossack Squat credit Adductors as a 0.5 secondary.","basis":"Inner-thigh adductors are the prime mover of the adductor machine and meaningful synergists in wide-stance/lateral work. Hip Abductor maps to Glutes (glute medius)."},
    {"exercise":"Cardio with real muscle work (Sled Push, Kettlebell Swing, Jump Squat, Burpee, Bear Crawl, Mountain Climber)","issue":"These train muscles but are tagged Cardio.","decision":"Tracked as cardio MINUTES only, not muscle sets.","basis":"Honors IRON's modality split (cardio = minutes). Conscious tradeoff; revisit if you want them dual-counted."},
    {"exercise":"All secondaries (0.5 factor)","issue":"Is 0.5 measured?","decision":"No — it's a modeling convention.","basis":"From Pelland et al.'s fractional-set meta-regression; a weighting choice, not a measured activation fraction. Disclose in any UI that cites the science."}
  ]
